  <object name="training hall">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <alias>Training Hall</alias>
    <description><![CDATA[Yesterday, a woman dressed in black cloaks and veils appeared in your village and invited you to take part in special training for the best rogues, mages, and fighters in Cognosco. You were shocked to receive her invitation, but you quickly accepted. Now you are standing in a huge room. You don't know how you got here, but it's easily the most impressive place you've ever seen.<br/><br/>Rich velvet banners hang from the wall. Marble pillars bracket you on either side. There are a few people in the room -- a mage and a fighter talking quietly in a corner, and a rogue sharpening a dagger while he chuckles to himself. There is one exit, a huge white gateway. The woman in the black cloak stands in front of it.]]></description>
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">7</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">3</attr>
    <attr name="grid_fill">SteelBlue</attr>
    <object name="player">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="editor_player" />
    </object>
    <object name="banners">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="plural" />
      <look>Red velvet banners hang from the walls. If you look closely, you can make out strange symbols woven into the threads.</look>
      <scenery />
      <takemsg>They are secured to the ceiling, at least ten meters above your head</takemsg>
    </object>
    <object name="pillars">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="plural" />
      <scenery />
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>marble pillars</value>
      </alt>
      <look>Tall and ancient pillars stand in various places along the room. There is a small box at the base of one of the pillars.</look>
      <takemsg>Not gonna happen</takemsg>
    </object>
    <object name="mage">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="male" />
      <look>A tall, thin mage with a long pointed beard stands against the west wall. His hands are hidden in his robes, and he carries a staff with a glowing globe on top.</look>
      <speak>The mage suddenly becomes very interested in his fingernails. He says: "Hmm. I don't have time for you. You should ASK the fighter ABOUT THE KEY, if that's what you're looking for." Rolling his eyes at the fighter, he adds, "Remind me not to sneak out again. The punishment is unbearable."</speak>
      <ask type="scriptdictionary">
        <item key="box closed spell reach through ">
          msg ("The mage stares at you. \"I am not here to teach foolish children party tricks.\"")
        </item>
      </ask>
    </object>
    <object name="fighter">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="female" />
      <look>A female fighter with short red hair is talking to the mage. A crystal sword hangs at her hip and she wears simple leather armor. She doesn't even look at you, but continues her conversation.</look>
      <speak>The fighter sighs and looks at you. "Yes? Was there something you wanted to ASK me ABOUT?"</speak>
      <ask type="scriptdictionary">
        <item key="key box keys scroll">
          msg ("The fighter sniffs and hands you a small key. \"Oh, I suppose you're looking for this.\"")
          AddToInventory (small key)
        </item>
      </ask>
      <object name="small key">
        <inherit name="editor_object" />
        <look>A small silver key. It has a strange gleam.</look>
        <take />
        <takemsg>The fighter hands you the key</takemsg>
        <dropmsg>You drop the small key</dropmsg>
        <feature_usegive />
        <use type="script">
          key box
        </use>
        <selfuseon type="scriptdictionary">
          <item key="box">
            key box
          </item>
        </selfuseon>
      </object>
    </object>
    <object name="rogue">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="male" />
      <look>The rogue grins at you in a way that makes you think he might be trying to decide how much money is in your coin purse. You decide to keep your distance.</look>
      <speak>His grin grows wider. "Don't waste my time if you have nothing of importance to ask me."</speak>
      <steal>The rogue glares at you. "I wouldn't try it, my friend."</steal>
      <ask type="scriptdictionary">
        <item key="key box keys">
          msg ("The rogue looks bored. \"If I had a key to something, I wouldn't be one to share it.\"")
        </item>
        <item key="scroll ">
          msg ("He laughs in delight. \"You're asking me about a scroll? That's like asking a duck about pizza. What's pizza, you say? It's this amazing concoction... like a piece 'o pie, but with cheese. Mmm... pizza.\"")
        </item>
      </ask>
    </object>
    <object name="cloaked woman">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="female" />
      <look type="script">
        if (Got(scroll)) {
          msg ("The cloaked woman inclines her head (you think). \"Ah,\" she says, her voice pleased, \"the Royal Scroll of Cognosco. Traveller, you may proceed into the training yard and through the portal.\"")
          UnlockExit (yard exit)
        }
        else {
          msg ("This is the same woman who appeared in your village the other day. You can't see her face behind her veil. Voluminous black robes sheath her entire body. You have no idea what she looks like, but she's definitely blocking the gateway. When you try to move past her, she shakes her head. \"Not without the magic scroll.\"")
        }
      </look>
      <speak type="script">
        if (Got(scroll)) {
          msg ("You think she smiles. \"Well done, child. You may now proceed to the NORTH.\" ")
          UnlockExit (yard exit)
        }
        else {
          msg ("She folds her arms. \"You may proceed no further without the scroll.\"")
        }
      </speak>
    </object>
    <object name="box">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="container_closed" />
      <inherit name="container_lockable" />
      <look>A very small box with a golden latch. It seems as if it was left here for you to find.</look>
      <feature_container />
      <hidechildren type="boolean">false</hidechildren>
      <listchildren />
      <listchildrenprefix>It contains</listchildrenprefix>
      <openmsg>You carefully open the box.</openmsg>
      <close type="boolean">false</close>
      <key type="object">small key</key>
      <onlock type="script">
        msg ("You use the small key to lock the box.")
      </onlock>
      <onunlock type="script">
        msg ("You use the small key to open the box and peer inside.")
      </onunlock>
      <open type="script">
        key box
      </open>
      <object name="scroll">
        <inherit name="editor_object" />
        <inherit name="openable" />
        <alias>strange scroll</alias>
        <look>A weathered parchment scroll sealed with a wax seal of Cognosco.</look>
        <alt type="stringlist">
          <value>magic scroll</value>
        </alt>
        <takemsg>You take the scroll.</takemsg>
        <dropmsg>You toss the scroll carelessly aside. Everyone in the room stops to glare. Slowly, you pick it up again.</dropmsg>
        <drop type="boolean">false</drop>
        <usedefaultprefix />
        <attr name="feature_usegive" type="boolean">false</attr>
        <attr name="feature_container" type="boolean">false</attr>
        <isopen type="boolean">false</isopen>
        <close type="script">
          if (GetBoolean(scroll, "read")) {
            msg ("You try to roll it up, but it's obvious you've tampered with it. Hopefully no one will notice.")
          }
          else {
            msg ("It's tightly rolled and sealed shut.")
          }
        </close>
        <take type="script">
          msg ("You pick up the scroll. It is sealed with wax and looks very old. The cloaked woman seems to turn towards you.")
          AddToInventory (scroll)
        </take>
        <ontake type="script">
          msg ("You tuck the scroll into the leather satchel at your side. The woman in black raises her head. You can't be sure, but you think she's looking at you.")
        </ontake>
        <openscript type="script">
          if (GetBoolean(scroll, "open")) {
            msg ("You can't read it again. Spoilers!")
          }
          else {
            msg ("Do you dare to break the seal of the kingdom of Cognosco? You hesitate, then unroll the scroll and lift it with shaky hands. What magical incantation might you learn? It says: \"Hello, Sweetie.\" Confused, you roll it up and seal it again.")
          }
        </openscript>
        <open type="script">
          if (not GetBoolean(scroll, "read")) {
            msg ("Do you dare to break the seal of the kingdom of Cognosco? You hesitate, then unroll the scroll and lift it with shaky hands. What magical incantation might you learn? It says: \"Hello, Sweetie.\" ")
            SetObjectFlagOn (scroll, "read")
          }
          else {
            msg ("You can't read it again. It might contain spoilers.")
          }
        </open>
      </object>
    </object>
    <exit alias="south" to="training hall">
      <inherit name="southdirection" />
      <lookonly />
      <look>You can see a long corridor and hear voices of students training. This is definitely the famous training hall of Cognosco, but you can't go that way right now.</look>
      <attr name="grid_length" type="int">10</attr>
    </exit>
    <exit name="yard exit" alias="north" to="training yard">
      <inherit name="northdirection" />
      <attr name="grid_length" type="int">0</attr>
      <locked />
      <lockmessage><![CDATA[The woman in black cloaks steps in front of you. "You may not pass this way without the magic scroll." <i> If you already have the scroll, try talking to the woman. If not, what are you waiting for? Go find it! </i>]]></lockmessage>
    </exit>
    <object name="gate">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>carved ivory doorway</alias>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>door</value>
        <value>gate</value>
        <value>doorway</value>
        <value>gateway</value>
        <value>doors</value>
        <value>doorways</value>
      </alt>
      <look>A huge set of double ivory doors stands behind the woman in the black cloak. They look like someone carved them by hand, and like they might lead somewhere important...</look>
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
      <open type="script">
        if (Got(scroll)) {
          msg ("The cloaked woman might be smiling. You think. \"You may now continue your journey by going NORTH,\" she says.")
          UnlockExit (yard exit)
        }
        else {
          msg ("The cloaked woman steps in front of you. \"You may not pass without the scroll,\" she says.")
        }
      </open>
    </object>
  </object>
  <verb>
    <property>open</property>
    <pattern>open; read; unroll</pattern>
    <defaultexpression>"You can't open; read; unroll " + object.article + "."</defaultexpression>
  </verb>
  <object name="training yard">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">7</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">5</attr>
    <attr name="grid_fill">Tan</attr>
    <alias>Training Yard</alias>
    <description><![CDATA[This is a huge, sprawling area. It is covered in dirt. You can see a fighting ring ahead of you, and some wooden practice swords along the wall. Under some trees are a circle of tree stumps. It looks like someone was conducting a class there. Someone has hung a large chalkboard. It reads:<br/><br/>COGNOSCO = DEMOCRACY<br/>IGNARUS = DICATORSHIP<br/><br/><i> Origins of the word democracy: <br/><br/>Demos = people<br/>Cratos = power or government </i><br/><br/>You marvel at these strange words before you find yourself staring at a woman standing in front of a glowing blue portal. It looks like the same woman you just talked to in the training hall. But then, the cloaks make it hard to tell.<br/>]]></description>
    <object name="fighting ring">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look>A circle is scratched in the dirt. You can see footprints where fighters have shuffled back and forth in training.</look>
      <scenery />
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>ring</value>
        <value>training ring</value>
      </alt>
    </object>
    <object name="dirt">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery />
      <look>You crawl on the ground and sniff the dirt before you realize what you're doing. Embarrassed, you stand up. </look>
      <takemsg>It's kind of gross.</takemsg>
    </object>
    <object name="swords">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>wooden swords</value>
        <value>sword</value>
        <value>training sword</value>
      </alt>
      <scenery />
      <look>Rough wooden swords lean against the wall. When you touch one, you expect to get a splinter, but the handles are worn smooth from years of use.</look>
      <takemsg>You pick up one of the swords. It is heavy and wooden, well worn from years of use. Thinking it might come in handy later, you tuck it into your belt.</takemsg>
      <dropmsg>You toss the wooden sword aside.</dropmsg>
      <attr name="feature_usegive" type="boolean">false</attr>
      <drop />
      <take type="script">
        training swords
      </take>
      <use type="script">
      </use>
      <steal type="script">
        training swords
      </steal>
      <object name="wooden sword">
        <inherit name="editor_object" />
        <take />
        <feature_usegive />
        <dropmsg>You toss the wooden sword aside.</dropmsg>
        <look>A heavy wooden sword used for training.</look>
        <takemsg>You pick up the wooden sword</takemsg>
        <alt type="stringlist">
          <value>sword</value>
        </alt>
        <use type="script">
          if (ListContains(ScopeVisible(), troll)) {
            msg ("You swing the sword in a fast arc. The troll tries to block it with his club, but he's too slow. The sword hits him on the head and he collapses to the ground, snoring softly. After a few seconds, he disappears.")
            MoveObject (troll, banners)
            UnlockExit (troll door)
            UnlockExit (exit behind troll)
          }
          else {
            msg ("You swing the sword wildly. After a few minutes of this, feeling rather tired and foolish, you put it away.")
          }
        </use>
        <selfuseanything type="script">
          msg ("You tap it with the sword. Nothing happens.")
        </selfuseanything>
        <attack type="script">
          if (ListContains(ScopeVisible(), troll)) {
            msg ("You swing the sword in a fast arc. The troll tries to block it with his club, but he's too slow. The sword hits him on the head and he collapses to the ground, snoring softly. After a few seconds, he disappears.")
            MoveObject (troll, banners)
            UnlockExit (troll door)
          }
          else {
            msg ("You swing the sword wildly. After a few minutes of this, feeling rather tired and foolish, you put it away.")
          }
        </attack>
        <selfuseon type="scriptdictionary">
          <item key="troll">
            if (ListContains(ScopeVisible(), troll)) {
              msg ("You swing the sword in a fast arc. The troll tries to block it with his club, but he's too slow. The sword hits him on the head and he collapses to the ground, snoring softly. After a few seconds, he disappears.")
              MoveObject (troll, banners)
              UnlockExit (troll door)
            }
            else {
              msg ("You swing the sword wildly. After a few minutes of this, feeling rather tired and foolish, you put it away.")
            }
          </item>
        </selfuseon>
      </object>
    </object>
    <object name="trees">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery />
      <look>There are trees around the edges of the training yard.</look>
    </object>
    <object name="stumps">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look>A circle of stumps surrounds a chalkboard. You nudge them with your foot, but they are neither magical nor portable.</look>
      <scenery />
      <siton>The stumps are uncomfortable. You're glad you don't have to go to school here.</siton>
    </object>
    <object name="chalkboard">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
      <look><![CDATA[COGNOSCO = DEMOCRACY<br/>IGNARUS = DICATORSHIP<br/><br/><i> Origins of the word democracy: <br/><br/>Demos = people<br/>Cratos = power or government </i><br/><br/>You marvel at these strange words.]]></look>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>board</value>
        <value>blackboard</value>
      </alt>
      <touch>With an evil grin, you go to erase the chalkboard. You jump back with a yelp as an electric shock jolts through your finger. You hear a chuckle, but when you look around, there is no one there.</touch>
      <drop type="boolean">false</drop>
      <takemsg>It's secured to the tree</takemsg>
    </object>
    <object name="woman">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="female" />
      <look>Is this also the same woman who appeared in your village the other day? You can't see her face behind her veil. Voluminous black robes sheath her entire body. You have no idea what she looks like.</look>
      <speak type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("The woman spreads her cloaked arms. \"Welcome, child,\" she says. She sounds EXACTLY like the woman from the training hall. Is it the same person? \"You are about to embark on a simple adventure. It should not challenge you greatly, but it will give you the experience you will need for... well, let's not speak of that now. Use the portal to proceed.\"<br/><br/>She smiles. \"Be careful: once the portal carries you away, you will need <b> the red key </b> to return. You won't be able to get it if you don't pay close attention to everything you see, hear, and read. You may even want to take notes. If you are prepared, go NORTH through the portal now.\"")
        UnlockExit (portal)
      ]]></speak>
    </object>
    <exit name="portal" alias="north" to="room of choosing">
      <inherit name="northdirection" />
      <locked />
      <lockmessage>Try talking to the woman first</lockmessage>
    </exit>
  </object>
  <object name="room of choosing">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <alias>Room of Choosing</alias>
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">3</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">3</attr>
    <description><![CDATA[You are in a plain white room. Walls, ceiling, floors -- they are pure white. The portal has vanished, leaving you trapped until you locate <b> the red key. </b> <br/><br/>To the east is a door with the royal crest of Cognosco.<br/><br/>To the west is a door bearing the mark of the dark King Nocens of Ignarus.<br/><br/>The room is otherwise empty.]]></description>
    <exit alias="west" to="ignarus">
      <inherit name="westdirection" />
      <attr name="grid_length" type="int">3</attr>
    </exit>
    <exit alias="east" to="cognosco">
      <inherit name="eastdirection" />
      <attr name="grid_length" type="int">3</attr>
    </exit>
  </object>
  <object name="ignarus">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <alias>Throne Room of Ignarus</alias>
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">4</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">4</attr>
    <attr name="grid_fill">SlateGrey</attr>
    <description><![CDATA[You are in what looks like, but cannot possibly be, the throne room of the kingdom of Ignarus. You shiver -- the room is very cold. There is a black iron throne in the middle of the room, surrounded by some dark liquid that you don't want to touch. The entire room seems to have been carved out of a gleaming black material. The only light comes from a globe hanging in the middle of the room. It shines a beam of welcome warmth over you and when you step into the beam, you smell the rich scents of home: meadows, baking bread, fresh fallen rain. <br/><br/>The throne seems to cast too many shadows. You remember that Ignarus is a dictatorship under the rule of King Nocens, and that this means he is the ultimate authority in that dark kingdom. He is the only one who makes decisions, and his word is law. You shudder, grateful that Cognosco allows its citizens so much freedom and participation in government.<br/><br/>To the northeast, a massive iron gate stands closed.]]></description>
    <exit alias="east" to="room of choosing">
      <inherit name="eastdirection" />
    </exit>
    <exit name="small hall exit" alias="northeast" to="small hall">
      <inherit name="northeastdirection" />
      <locked />
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
    </exit>
    <object name="throne">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
      <sit>You approach the throne. The temperature drops and you begin to shiver. When you turn your back on the chair, you have the uncomfortable sense you are being watched. You slowly sit on the throne, and it burns through your clothes. You leap to your feet, checking for damage, but you seem to be fine.</sit>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>chair</value>
        <value>seat</value>
      </alt>
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <look type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (Got(large black key)) {
          msg ("The throne is no longer cold to the touch. You can see the words \"power to the people\" in white under the globe's light.")
        }
        else {
          msg ("The throne is made of a heavy black metal twisted into shapes and letters.  You can make out words on the back: <i> Ignarus, Nocens, dictatorship. </i> ")
        }
      ]]></look>
    </object>
    <object name="pool">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
      <look>A shining pool of some thick black liquid surrounds the throne. A stone bridge allows you to cross over it without getting wet.</look>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>water</value>
        <value>liquid</value>
      </alt>
      <touch>You crouch down and reach towards the pool. Cold air rises around you, along with a foul smell. You decide you'd rather not put your fingers in there.</touch>
      <swim>You crouch down and reach towards the pool. Cold air rises around you, along with a foul smell. You decide you'd rather not put your fingers in there.</swim>
      <drink>You crouch down and reach towards the pool. Cold air rises around you, along with a foul smell. You decide you'd rather not put your fingers in there.</drink>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <object name="globe">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>light</value>
        <value>lamp</value>
      </alt>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <look type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (Got(large black key)) {
          msg ("The globe shines its warm light on the throne of Ignarus. It no longer looks so intimdating.")
        }
        else {
          msg ("The globe emits a warm glow. You can see the word <i> Cognosco </i> on it, perhaps magically engraved. It looks like you might be able to TURN it.")
        }
      ]]></look>
      <turn type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (GetBoolean(globe, "turned")) {
          msg ("The globe refuses to budge. ")
        }
        else {
          msg ("You carefully grasp the globe in both hands. As you turn it, the beam of light sweeps through the dark room. At last it falls on the throne. The word <i> dictatorship </i> shifts until the letters say <i> power to the people </i> instead. A large black key falls from the globe. You bend to pick it up.")
          AddToInventory (large black key)
          UnlockExit (small hall exit)
        }
      ]]></turn>
      <object name="large black key">
        <inherit name="editor_object" />
        <look>A heavy black iron key</look>
        <alt type="stringlist">
          <value>key</value>
        </alt>
        <take />
        <takemsg>You pick up the iron key. It has the same pattern as those carved into the gate in the Ignarus Throne Room.</takemsg>
        <dropmsg>You toss the key aside.</dropmsg>
        <feature_usegive />
        <use type="script">
          ignarus key
        </use>
      </object>
    </object>
    <object name="gate1">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>gate</alias>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <look type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (Got(large black key)) {
          msg ("The heavy iron gates stand open, revealing a narrow corridor beyond")
        }
        else {
          msg ("A huge gate carved from the same metal as the throne. When you look closer, you see a verse carved into the door:<br/><br/><i> The people of Ignarus<br/>Are cold and alone<br/>Shine the light of Cognosco<br/>On the darkest of thrones </i>")
        }
      ]]></look>
      <open type="script">
        ignarus key
      </open>
    </object>
    <object name="walls">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="plural" />
      <scenery />
      <look>The walls are carved from some shiny material. You touch it and find it as cold and smooth as black glass.</look>
    </object>
  </object>
  <object name="cognosco">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <alias>Throne Room of Cognosco</alias>
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">4</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">4</attr>
    <attr name="grid_fill">SkyBlue</attr>
    <description><![CDATA[You are in what looks like, but cannot possibly be, the throne room of the kingdom of Cognosco. A large white throne dominates the room where the king would usually sit. However, you recall that in the year 1215, King John signed the <i> Magna Carta, </i> or Great Charter, transforming Cognosco into a <i> constitutional monarchy </i> -- a democracy, where the power lies in the hands of the people.<br/><br/>That means that in Cognosco, even though the king is the head of the government, the people are the ones truly in charge. In front of King Ion's throne sits a round table with space for twelve representatives, elected from the provinces of Cognosco. You excitedly find the chair labeled <i> Praesto, </i>, the name of your home province. You know that a local shopkeeper named Minerva was elected to this position. She is your province's voice in the government.<br/><br/>Aside from the gleaming white throne and the round table, the walls are white marble. The crest of Cognosco hangs behind the throne. Two smaller thrones sit to the side. Princess Lenis often occupies the one on the right. Before her death, the Queen Mother sat in the one to the left. A large white gate leads to the north. ]]></description>
    <exit alias="west" to="room of choosing">
      <inherit name="westdirection" />
    </exit>
    <exit name="northern gateway" alias="north" to="layer room">
      <inherit name="northdirection" />
      <locked />
    </exit>
    <object name="large throne">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look>King Ion VI of Cognosco currently uses this throne. It is beautiful and awe inspiring. However, it is also not the true seat of power. That belongs to the twelve chairs surrounding the table.</look>
      <sit>You climb the steps to King Ion VI's throne with bated breath, but find you do not quite have the nerve to sit on it.</sit>
      <touch>You run your fingers over the throne's delicate carvings, marveling that centuries of Cognosco's greatest rulers have sat in this very throne.</touch>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <object name="lenis throne">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>small throne to the right</alias>
      <look>This is a soft cushioned seat often occupied by Her Majesty Princess Lenis.</look>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <siton>You carefully lower yourself into the seat. For just a moment, you think you see people in the twelve seats around the table, their heads swiveled towards you. Then the vision fades away.</siton>
      <touch>The throne is gold plated. Its cushions are surprisingly soft and comfortable.</touch>
      <scenery />
    </object>
    <object name="mother throne">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>small throne to the left</alias>
      <look>This is a soft cushioned seat formerly occupied by the Queen Mother, who passed away last winter.</look>
      <scenery />
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <siton>You carefully settle yourself onto the throne. A memory of King Ion's and Princess Lenis' mother overwhelms you: a gentle, soft spoken, and wise woman, Queen Conscientia ruled for thirty four years before stepping aside in favor of her son, Ion VI. </siton>
      <touch>The throne is silver plated. Its cushions are surprisingly soft and comfortable.</touch>
    </object>
    <object name="crest of cognosco">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery />
      <alias>Crest of Cognosco</alias>
      <look>The crest of Cognosco hangs from a bright banner behind the thrones. It shows the letter C circled by Cognosco's famous black pearls.</look>
      <touch>It is soft and well worn. You wonder how long ago it was embroidered, and how it has come to be so well preserved.</touch>
    </object>
    <object name="chairs">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="plural" />
      <scenery />
      <look>Twelve chairs surround a wooden table.</look>
      <siton>They are more comfortable than they look.</siton>
    </object>
    <object name="wooden table">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <scenery type="boolean">false</scenery>
      <look>The large wooden table is rough and uneven, but perfectly circular. This symbolizes that no one at the table is more important than anyone else. Although King Ion VI is the official leader, everyone in a democracy has an equal voice.</look>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
    </object>
    <object name="praesto chair">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <look><![CDATA[This is the chair where Minerva, the current representative from your province, sits when the government is in session. The people of your province <b>elected</b> her to <b>represent</b> them in the government.]]></look>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>province chair</value>
        <value>special chair</value>
        <value>my chair</value>
      </alt>
      <alias>Chair for the Representative of Praesto</alias>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <siton type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("You settle yourself in the wooden chair. Suddenly, the room springs to life. A man across from you is standing and loudly arguing. The other chairs are full, and their occupants are nodding or shaking their heads. You hear a sound, and turn to see King Ion VI himself in his throne, his hands held up for silence. \"Enough!\" He says. \"We've heard both sides of the issue. Representatives of Cognosco, it is time to vote.\"<br/><br/>The vision fades.  You shake your head and realize that there is now a large white key sitting on the table in front of you. You pick it up and turn it over in your hands before putting it in your pocket.")
        UnlockExit (northern gateway)
        AddToInventory (large white key)
      ]]></siton>
    </object>
    <object name="gate2">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <alias>gate</alias>
      <visible />
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>exit</value>
        <value>door</value>
      </alt>
      <look type="script"><![CDATA[
        if (Got(large white key)) {
          msg ("The gate stands open, leading into another room.")
        }
        else {
          msg ("A large white gate, much like the one in the training hall. It is locked. When you look more closely, you see a verse engraved on it:<br/><br/><i> A representative democracy<br/>Asks each to become part of me<br/>Choose the one who represents you<br/>Who votes and sees decisions through<br/>And then at last, if you are able<br/>Take your seat at the round table </i><br/><br/>HINT: If you are stuck in this room, try ASKing THE GATE about THE PUZZLE. It sounds strange, but it just might work.")
        }
      ]]></look>
      <ask type="scriptdictionary">
        <item key="puzzle">
          msg ("There is a deep rumble from somewhere, you don't know where, and a voice speaks all around you, saying: \"Have you tried SITting ON THE CHAIR? Just saying 'sit' isn't going to cut it, you know.\"")
        </item>
      </ask>
    </object>
  </object>
