  <object name="constitution">
    <inherit name="editor_room" />
    <attr name="grid_width" type="int">4</attr>
    <attr name="grid_length" type="int">4</attr>
    <alias>Emerald Room</alias>
    <description><![CDATA[The room is blindingly green. When you look closer, you think it may have actually been carved out of a huge emerald, although that is clearly impossible. Although... when you remember some of the "tricks" mages have performed in your village, you have to wonder. Are you sure you chose the right class?<br/><br/>The only thing in the room -- aside from a whole lot of green -- is a pedestal in its center. The pedestal also seems like it was carved from marble. You approach and see that there is a clear glass lid covering a piece of paper. The glass lid has a circular space that looks like you can press something into it.]]></description>
    <attr name="grid_fill">SpringGreen</attr>
    <exit alias="southwest" to="troll hall">
      <inherit name="southwestdirection" />
    </exit>
    <object name="glass lid">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="container_closed" />
      <inherit name="container_lockable" />
      <look><![CDATA[A clear glass lid covers the pedestal. There is a round indendation about the size of a medallion. It looks like you could put something in there.<br/><br/>Beneath the lid, you can see a weathered paper. Looking closely, you can make out the words <i> Constitution of Cognosco </i> in fancy writing. Your heart skips a beat. Is this really the Consititution, the document that holds the greatest laws of the country, that holds the Charter of Rights and Freedoms and guarantees every citizen's rights? If so, this is the very document that makes Cognosco different from Ignarus.]]></look>
      <alt type="stringlist">
        <value>cover</value>
      </alt>
      <useindividualverblist type="boolean">false</useindividualverblist>
      <usestandardverblist />
      <displayverbs type="stringlist">
        <value>Look at</value>
      </displayverbs>
      <feature_container />
      <close type="boolean">false</close>
      <transparent />
      <listchildren />
      <listchildrenprefix>It contains</listchildrenprefix>
      <autounlock type="boolean">false</autounlock>
      <unlockmessage><![CDATA[The glass lid has vanished. There is a weathered paper on the pedestal. You stare in reverence at the <i> Constitution of Cognosco. </i> This is the ultimate law of the land, containing the Charter of Rights and Freedoms. It gives everyone in Cognosco rights, responsibilities, and freedoms, and it is what makes you different from Ignarus. ]]></unlockmessage>
      <lockmessage>The glass lid is locked firmly in place.</lockmessage>
      <nokeymessage>You do not have anything that fits the circular indentation.</nokeymessage>
      <usedefaultprefix />
      <isopen />
      <autoopen />
      <key type="object">citizenship medallion</key>
      <onopen type="script"><![CDATA[
        msg ("You stare in reverence at the <i> Constitution of Cognosco. </i> This is the ultimate law of the land, containing the Charter of Rights and Freedoms. It gives everyone in Cognosco rights, responsibilities, and freedoms, and it is what makes you different from Ignarus. ")
      ]]></onopen>
      <object name="weathered paper">
        <inherit name="editor_object" />
        <take />
        <takemsg>With shaking hands, you roll the constitution and place it in your belt. You are now carrying with you the rights and freedoms of every person in Cognosco.</takemsg>
        <drop type="boolean">false</drop>
        <dropmsg>Who would want to lose such an important piece of paper?</dropmsg>
        <usestandardverblist />
        <alt type="stringlist">
          <value>constitution</value>
        </alt>
        <look type="script"><![CDATA[
          if (Got(weathered paper)) {
            msg ("This is the Consitution of Cognosco. A constitution is the ultimate law of the land, the things and principles which <i> constitute, </i> or make up, the country.")
          }
          else {
            msg ("The Constitution of Cognosco lies on the pedestal.")
          }
        ]]></look>
      </object>
    </object>
    <object name="pedestal">
      <inherit name="editor_object" />
      <inherit name="container_closed" />
